I rang, Mr. Fawlty,
I must speak with you.

575
00:25:13,347 --> 00:25:15,933
- Can't you see I'm busy?
- It's very important.

576
00:25:16,183 --> 00:25:16,975
- Can we talk in there?
- I can't.

577
00:25:17,226 --> 00:25:18,810
- Basil!
- It's very important!

578
00:25:19,061 --> 00:25:22,606
I'm dealing with something
important out here, Sybil.

579
00:25:22,856 --> 00:25:27,152
Yes? Yes, right, well,
yes, yes, what is it?

580
00:25:27,402 --> 00:25:28,195
- It's about Lord Melbury.
- Yes?

581
00:25:28,445 --> 00:25:29,780
He's not
Lord Melbury,

582
00:25:30,030 --> 00:25:31,406
he's a confidence
trickster.

583
00:25:31,657 --> 00:25:32,950
I beg your pardon?

584
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:34,076
Mr. Brown told me.

585
00:25:34,326 --> 00:25:35,327
Oh!

586
00:25:35,577 --> 00:25:36,787
Mr. Brown's
from the C.I.D.

587
00:25:37,037 --> 00:25:38,413
They've been
watching Melbury

588
00:25:38,664 --> 00:25:40,249
because he's pulling some
big con trick in the town.

589
00:25:40,499 --> 00:25:42,084
They're going to arrest
him when he leaves here,

590
00:25:42,334 --> 00:25:43,544
so as not to cause
you embarrassment.

591
00:25:43,794 --> 00:25:44,795
But he asked me
to tell you...

592
00:25:45,045 --> 00:25:46,171
Oh, how nice of him!

593
00:25:46,421 --> 00:25:47,422
Please, Mr. Fawlty...

594
00:25:47,673 --> 00:25:48,799
Oh, I don't know
what other tales

595
00:25:49,049 --> 00:25:50,759
Mr. Brown of M.I.5 has been
impressing you with.

596
00:25:51,009 --> 00:25:52,970
- He's a con man!
- Oh, yes, of course,

597
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:54,012
it stands out
a mile, doesn't it?

598
00:25:54,263 --> 00:25:55,556
He's so common.

599
00:25:55,806 --> 00:26:00,602
Unlike that cockney git
whose ulterior motive

600
00:26:01,019 --> 00:26:03,772
poor, innocent,
misguided child that you are.

601
00:26:04,022 --> 00:26:04,857
Basil, what's
going on?

602
00:26:05,107 --> 00:26:06,358
Nothing, my dear,
nothing at all.

603
00:26:06,608 --> 00:26:08,193
- Mrs. Fawlty...
- Yes, Polly?

604
00:26:08,443 --> 00:26:10,153
- I don't know what she's...
- Basil!

605
00:26:10,404 --> 00:26:11,947
Mr. Brown is
from the C.I.D.

606
00:26:12,197 --> 00:26:14,199
He showed me
identification.

607
00:26:14,449 --> 00:26:16,577
They're watching Melbury.
He's a confidence trickster.

608
00:26:16,827 --> 00:26:17,911
I see.

609
00:26:18,162 --> 00:26:19,538
What do you mean,
you see?

610
00:26:19,788 --> 00:26:21,165
Let's have a look
at these valuables.

611
00:26:21,415 --> 00:26:22,207
What are you
doing, Sybil?

612
00:26:22,457 --> 00:26:23,542
Sybil, I forbid you
to open that safe!

613
00:26:23,792 --> 00:26:25,919
Sybil, I forbid you
to take that case out!

614
00:26:26,170 --> 00:26:30,299
Sybil, do not open
that case, I forbid it!

615
00:26:30,549 --> 00:26:31,925
I never thought I would
live to see the day

616
00:26:32,176 --> 00:26:34,720
when a peer
of the realm,

617
00:26:34,970 --> 00:26:37,097
entrusts to us,
a case of valuables...

618
00:26:37,347 --> 00:26:40,100
In trust...

619
00:27:04,625 --> 00:27:05,459
I'll call the police.

620
00:27:05,709 --> 00:27:09,213
They're already here,
Mr. Brown's outside.

621
00:27:09,796 --> 00:27:12,841
Someone at
reception, Basil?

622
00:27:22,351 --> 00:27:25,229
Ah! All right.

623
00:27:25,479 --> 00:27:29,149
Ah... Good evening.

624
00:27:29,399 --> 00:27:30,442
I believe you
were expecting us.

625
00:27:30,692 --> 00:27:31,652
No, I was expecting
somebody else.

626
00:27:31,902 --> 00:27:33,570
Sir Richard
and Lady Morris.

627
00:27:33,820 --> 00:27:34,738
Yes, yes, them as well.

628
00:27:34,988 --> 00:27:35,781
I'm sorry?

629
00:27:36,031 --> 00:27:37,199
- How did you know?
- What?

630
00:27:37,449 --> 00:27:38,909
Oh... You're Sir Richard
and Lady Morris,

631
